(456, 'MTUwNTg2MTI5OTo3Njk0Nzoy', 'Related Info', 'Fibers from stems used in numerous historic objects, including coarse bags, fabrics and split bark bags of Ohio cave and rock-shelter dwellers, a bag from the Menomini where the pawpaw fiber is used only in the weft, a Potawatomi bag. Its use seems only limited by its distribution', 'Whitford 1941', '1941', '', '', 0, 2, 'Whitford 1941')
