(513, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMDo0OTA2Nzoy', 'Related Info', 'The Peoria term cited by Dunn (ca.1909) for pignut hickory tree is also used by the Eastern Miami as a generic for all hickory trees; 6. Perrot describes a nut about 2 inches long that is bitter and oily and inedible which could be referring to the pignut, although it is not that bitter', 'Perrot 1680-1718', '1680-1718', '', '', 0, 2, 'Perrot 1680-1718, translation from French to English by Blair 1911:119')
