(615, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMDoyMDM3ODoy', 'Related Info', 'Allouez remarked about the Illinois\' use of bow and arrow: \"They ordinarily carry only the warclub, bow, and a quiver full of arrows, which they discharge so adroitly and quickly, that men armed with guns, have hardly time to raise them to the shoulder. They also carry a large buckler made of skins of wild cattle; which is arrow-proof, and covers the whole body\"', 'Allouez 1677', '1677', '', '', 0, 2, 'Allouez 1677, from Shea 1903:78')
