(637, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMDo3NTA4MDoy', 'Related Info', 'Cratageus spp. Are most commonly called \'hawthorns\', some are black, called black hawthorns, and some are red, called redhaws. Blackhaws are usually referring to Viburnum prunifolium, not Cratageus spp. Hawthorn uses include Meskwaki (drug, food/fruit), Ojibway (food/fruits, drug/root), Potawatomi (drug/berry, food/berry)', 'Cratageus 2006', '2006', '', '', 0, 2, 'Gonella\'s note, 7/2006')
