(639, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMDo4MTA2NDoy', 'Use - Medicinal', 'roots used to cure eye problems. \"The root of the wild chervil is marvelous for illnesses of the eyes, by dropping in the eye water in which this root has steeped, in the month of May when the vine is in sap\"', 'Anonymous 1724', '1724', '', '', 0, 0, 'Anonymous 1724:163B, \"La Racine Cerfeuil Savage est merveilleuse pour le maux des yeux, en faisant de gouter dans l\'oiel l\'eau dans la quelle a rompre la Racine, dans le mois de May quand la Vigne est en Seve\", translation from French to English by Poirier 2004; the author is describing tribal customs from the upper Midwest, probably including some of the Miami-Illlinois tribal groups')
