(821, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMjoyNTA2Nzoy', 'Ecological Info', '\"A lot of hazelnut around [then]\" \"they don\'t seem to grow very good any more, the hazelnuts do, likewise with butternuts. I don\'t know whether they [people] going after the wood of the butternut trees or what cause it but the butternut just seemed to die out. The butternuts you\'d pretty near had to fight with the squirrels to get \'em, cause they really, I mean they really ate the butternuts. If one falls out, . . .if one drop out of a tree there were a couple of squirrels watching . . . \"', 'Tippmann 1999', '1999', '', '', 0, 1, 'Interview with Jim Strack, Tippman 1999')
(822, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMjoyNTA2Nzoy', 'Related Info', 'Also known as \'sinkisisa\'', 'Hockett 1938', '1938', '', '', 0, 2, 'Hockett 1938')
(823, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMjoyNTA2Nzoy', 'Related Info', '\"The Potawatomie Indians drank a tea made from the inner bark of the butternut for stomach upsets\"', 'McPherson 1977', '1977', '', '', 0, 2, 'McPherson 1977:57, 2ndy source without primary source citation')
