(897, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMjo5OTIyNDoy', 'Use - Medicinal', 'tea used as a tonic. \"My mother used to use it, besides making spicebush tea, she used it to parboil older game like an old \'coon or an old woodchuck. To parboil \'em in it, it tenderized \'em. Or at least we thought it did.\"', 'Marks 1989', '1989', '', '', 0, 0, 'Interview with Lamoine Marks, Rafert 1989:103')
(898, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMjo5OTIyNDoy', 'Use - Medicinal', 'root tea used \"for everything you know\"', 'Walker, Olds, Olds, Tippman 1999', '1999', '', '', 0, 0, 'Interview with Mildred Walker, Olds, Olds and Tippman 1999')
(899, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMjo5OTIyNDoy', 'Use - Medicinal', 'stems used to make tea. \"The Indians cut the stems into sticks or small pieces pour hot water over them and drink the infusion as spicewood tea\"', 'Gatschet 1895', '1895', '', '', 0, 0, 'Gatschet ca. 1895:2658')
