(1322, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNDo1NTg2MDoy', 'Habitat', 'There are six native currant species. Five of these species (Spiny swamp-currant, R. lacustre; Skunk-currant, R. glandulosum; Western black currant, R. hudsonianum; Eastern black currant, R. americanum; Swamp red currant, R. triste) occur in wet areas including swamps, bogs, woods in the eastern Miami lands. A sixth native species (Buffalo-currant, R. odoratum) occurs on rocky cliffs and hillsides predominately in western Miami lands. Two exotic currants (Garden black currant, R. nigrum; Garden red currant, R. sativum) occur as escapes from areas where cultivated throughout eastern and western Miami lands.;', 'Gleason and Cronquist 1991', '1991', '', '', 0, 1, 'Gleason and Cronquist 1991')
