(1396, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNTo5NTE5NToy', 'Horticultural Info', 'Village location sometimes was chosen for its nearness to an abundance of root crops that attracted vast numbers of birds in the autumn when the marshes were dry. These root crops were quite possibly arrowhead, and the Illinois probably placed their village close to the portion of the lake that had an abundance of tubers available', 'Pease 1934', '1934', '', '', 0, 0, 'Pease 1934:350, Deliette 1721, \"y en a une si grande quantite dans la Riviere et principalement dans le Lac au bout duquel les Illiois sont Etablis du coste du nord a cause de la quantite de Racine qu\'il,\" translation from French to English by Pease')
(1397, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNTo5NTE5NToy', 'Ecological Info', '\"We camped near where the Shawnee hills now stand, from which point to the Indianola ferry where the bridge now spans the Kaw, was a swamp or dry lake, and in this lake the wild potatoes grew in abundance. As we laid ourselves down to sleep that night our lullaby was the crunch of the wild hog as he masticated the wild potato, of which he was very fond\"', 'Myaamiaki 1998', '1998', '', '', 0, 0, 'Aatotankiki Myaamiaki, 1(2):2, 1998, from Ely Moore 1908')
(1398, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNTo5NTE5NToy', 'Related Info', '\"Topeka\" means \"a place to find small or wild potatoes\" in the Kaw language', 'Myaamiaki 1998', '1998', '', '', 0, 2, 'Aatotankiki Myaamiaki, 1(2):2, 1998--Ely Moore 1908')
(1399, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNTo5NTE5NToy', 'Related Info', 'Robert Vezina has determined that the word \'8abissipena\' is the Illinois word for an edible arrowhead', 'Vezina 2002', '2002', '', '', 0, 2, 'Vezina 2002, pers. comm.')
(1400, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNTo5NTE5NToy', 'Related Info', 'Gravier used the Ojibwe/Algonquin term for arrowhead to translate the Illinois term, implying that historically the same word referred to Sagittaria latifolia, in both languages. In Ojibwe, the word \'waabiziipin\' appears to mean swan potato, however the word has no morpheme for \'water\' in it. There is still some discussion about the Miami word and its actual meaning', 'McCafferty, Costa, Fiero 2003', '2003', '', '', 0, 2, 'Gravier ca.1700, Email discussion between McCafferty, Costa and Fiero, February 21, 2003')
