(1584, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNjo1MDkzOjI=', 'Related Info', 'An ancient fishing weir dam still exists on the Wabash River, northeast of Peru, Indiana and was and is known to most Miami fishermen. Lamoine Marks was told about it when he was a boy, by his father Charlie, and last saw it while fishing in winter in 1953. Rafert and Marks rediscovered it in July, 1988. This weir dam is described in Outdoor Indiana, July/August 1989', 'Marks 1989', '1989', '', '', 0, 2, 'Interview with Lamoine Marks, Rafert 1989:47')
