(1597, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNjo2MzY3Njoy', 'Use - Unknown', '\"ashushuwia, nettle, or species of weed, the leaves of which produce a burning or itching juice and are hence regarded as poisonous. They bear no flower, the stalk is about 1 foot tall\"', 'Gatschet 1895', '1895', '', '', 0, 0, 'Gatschet ca. 1895')
(1598, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNjo2MzY3Njoy', 'Related Info', 'Although no use is mentioned by Dunn or Gatschet for this species, the fact that a word was recorded leaves open the question if this nettle was also used for fiber. It is possible, but it would be a less desirable species due to its short stature and hence, shorter fibers', 'Gonella', '', '', '', 0, 2, 'Gonella\'s note')
