(1628, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNjo2NjY1NDoy', 'Use - Medicinal', 'medicinal plant. \"It was also used in the case of wounds, or something like that\"', 'Marks 1989', '1989', '', '', 0, 0, 'Interview with Lamoine Marks, Rafert 1989:94-95')
(1629, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNjo2NjY1NDoy', 'Use - Medicinal', 'mullein leaves used for bee stings', 'Lamb and Shultz 1964', '1964', '', '', 0, 0, 'Lamb and Shultz 1964:38, information in publication from Clarence Godfroy')
(1630, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNjo2NjY1NDoy', 'Use - Medicinal', 'leaves used to treat sores, infections. The leaves were used on sores to draw out the poison and infection. \"Used more than poultices [for infections]\"', 'Strack 1999', '1999', '', '', 0, 0, 'Interview with Jim Strack, Tippman 1999')
(1631, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNjo2NjY1NDoy', 'Use - Medicinal', 'leaves gathered, cut into strips and boiled in water to make vapor for treating kids with a strong cough. Adults can roll dried leaves and smoke to cure strong cough', 'Tippman 2005', '2005', '', '', 0, 0, 'Interview with Dani Tippman, Gonella 2005')
(1632, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNjoyNzk2OjI=', 'Habitat', 'Occurs in moist fields, meadows, prairies and swamps throughout eastern and western Miami lands', 'Gleason and Cronquist 1991', '1991', '', '', 0, 0, 'Gleason and Cronquist 1991')
(1633, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNjoyNzk2OjI=', 'Use - Food', 'human-charred Vervain material was recovered from an early 19th century Miami village site at the forks of the Wabash River', 'Bush 1996', '2003', '', '', 0, 0, 'Bush 1996:181')
